  NBS-030 | NATIONAL ID CARD PDF GENERATION
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  Owner  : Member 1 (Backend) + Member 2 (Mobile — print trigger)
  Points : 5

  USER STORY:
  As a Village Officer, after completing citizen registration I can generate
  a National ID card as a PDF that the citizen can print, valid for 10 years.

  ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA:
  Given a citizen registration is completed successfully
  When the officer taps "Generate National ID Card"
  Then a PDF is generated with: citizen photo, full name, NID number,
       date of birth, gender, issue date, expiry date (issued + 10 years)
       and a signed QR code linking to the national registry
  And the PDF is stored in Cloudinary and the URL returned to the officer
  And the citizen record is updated: national_id_issued + national_id_expires
  And the PDF is viewable on the mobile device and shareable

  TASKS — BACKEND:
  [ ] Install pdf-lib and qrcode: npm install pdf-lib qrcode
  [ ] Create backend/src/services/id-card.service.js
  [ ] Load NBS ID card template (design a basic A4 PDF layout using pdf-lib)
  [ ] Fill fields: photo (embed as JPEG), NID, full name, DOB, gender,
      issue date, expiry date (issued + 10 years)
  [ ] Generate QR code: qrcode.toBuffer({ data: nidNumber, signature: sign(nidNumber) })
  [ ] Embed QR code in PDF
  [ ] Upload PDF to Cloudinary (census_pdfs folder)
  [ ] Update citizen: national_id_issued = today, national_id_expires = today+10yr
  [ ] Create POST /api/citizens/:citizenId/generate-id-card
  [ ] Write Jest test with mock pdf-lib and Cloudinary

  TASKS — MOBILE (Officer App):
  [ ] Add "Generate ID Card" button on registration success screen
  [ ] Show loading indicator while PDF is generated server-side
  [ ] On success: display PDF viewer (expo-pdf-viewer or WebView)
  [ ] Share button: allow officer to share PDF via WhatsApp / print


