  NBS-032 + NBS-033 | BIRTH REGISTRATION + NATIONAL ID GENERATION
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  Owner  : Member 1 (Backend) + Member 2 (Mobile — hospital officer app)
  Points : 8  (NBS-032: 5pts + NBS-033: 3pts)

  USER STORY:
  As a Hospital Officer, I can register a newborn's birth with their details
  and parent National IDs so the system creates a citizen record and issues
  a unique National ID for the child.

  ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA:
  Given I am a Hospital Officer inside my facility geo-fence
  When I navigate to "Register Birth"
  Then I can enter: child first name, middle name, surname, gender, date of birth
  And I enter Father National ID → system verifies father exists in DB
  And I enter Mother National ID → system verifies mother exists in DB
  And my facility_id is auto-attached from my officer profile
  And my officer ID is linked as the delivery officer
  And on submit: the system generates a unique National ID for the newborn
  And a citizen record is created with vital_status=ALIVE, age tracking starts
  And a birth record is created in the births table
  And the citizen_children table is updated for both parents

  NATIONAL ID GENERATION RULES:
  Format: TZ-YYYY-XXXXXXXX (year of birth + 8-digit padded sequence number)
  Must be globally unique — use DB sequence or UUID-to-numeric conversion

  TASKS — BACKEND:
  [ ] Create POST /api/births with auth guard (hospital_officer only)
  [ ] Validate: facility_id matches officer's facility
  [ ] Look up father NID + mother NID in citizens table
  [ ] Generate unique NID: TZ-{birthYear}-{padStart(sequence, 8, '0')}
      Use PostgreSQL sequence: CREATE SEQUENCE nid_seq START 10000000
  [ ] Insert citizen record (child) with:
      national_id = generated, vital_status=ALIVE, father/mother links
  [ ] Insert birth record (facility_id, officer_id, father/mother citizen_ids)
  [ ] Insert citizen_children rows for father and mother
  [ ] Return birth_id and generated national_id
  [ ] Write Jest tests

  TASKS — MOBILE (Hospital Officer App):
  [ ] Create BirthRegistrationScreen:
      Fields: first_name, middle_name, surname, gender radio, date_of_birth (date picker)
      Father NID input + verify button → show father name on verify
      Mother NID input + verify button → show mother name on verify
  [ ] Submit → show success screen with generated NID
  [ ] "Generate Birth Certificate" button → triggers NBS-034


