  NBS-036 + NBS-037 + NBS-038 | DEATH REGISTRATION (ALL CASES)
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  Owner  : Member 1 (Backend) + Member 2 (Mobile — both officer apps)
  Points : 13  (NBS-036: 3, NBS-037: 5, NBS-038: 5)

  USER STORY A (NBS-036) — Village Officer:
  As a Village Officer, I can register a death that occurred outside a
  hospital by entering the citizen's National ID, date of death, and cause.

  USER STORY B (NBS-037) — Hospital Officer:
  As a Hospital Officer, I can register an in-hospital death for either
  an adult citizen or an infant (using parent NIDs).

  USER STORY C (NBS-038) — System actions on death:
  As the system, when a death is registered I update the citizen's status,
  freeze their age, generate a death certificate, and push to RITA.

  ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA (Combined):
  OUTSIDE HOSPITAL (Village Officer):
  → Enter citizen NID → fetch citizen info → confirm details
  → Enter date of death, cause of death
  → On submit: citizen vital_status = DECEASED, age frozen
  → Death certificate generated, RITA push attempted

  INSIDE HOSPITAL — ADULT (Hospital Officer):
  → Enter citizen NID → fetch citizen info
  → Enter cause of death, date of death
  → Enter duty doctor/nurse NID (linked to officer record)
  → On submit: citizen vital_status = DECEASED, age frozen
  → Certificate generated, RITA push

  INSIDE HOSPITAL — INFANT (Hospital Officer):
  → Select "Infant" category
  → Enter mother NID + father NID (verify both exist)
  → Enter date of death, cause if applicable
  → No citizen record to update (infant never had full registration)
  → Certificate generated (infant death cert), RITA push

  TASKS — BACKEND:
  [ ] Create POST /api/deaths with auth (village_officer OR hospital_officer)
  [ ] Body: { citizenNid?, category, locationType, causeOfDeath, dateOfDeath,
              dutyOfficerNid?, infantFatherNid?, infantMotherNid?, facilityId? }
  [ ] Validation: hospital_officer cannot register outside-hospital deaths
  [ ] Validation: village_officer cannot register in-hospital deaths
  [ ] On adult/outside death: UPDATE citizens SET vital_status=DECEASED
      (do NOT change age — leave as current value, frozen)
  [ ] Generate death certificate PDF (similar to birth cert service)
  [ ] Push to RITA mock API
  [ ] Set rita_synced flag
  [ ] Write Jest tests for all three cases

  TASKS — MOBILE (Village Officer App):
  [ ] Add "Register Death" menu item in village officer app
  [ ] NID entry → citizen preview card → date picker + cause text input
  [ ] Submit → show death certificate download option

  TASKS — MOBILE (Hospital Officer App):
  [ ] Add "Register Death" menu item
  [ ] Category selector: Infant / Adult
  [ ] Adult: NID entry → cause + date + duty officer NID
  [ ] Infant: father NID + mother NID + date + cause
  [ ] Submit → certificate download


