  NBS-039 + NBS-040 + NBS-041 + NBS-042 | MARRIAGE REGISTRATION
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  Owner  : Member 1 (Backend) + Member 2 (Mobile — village officer app)
  Points : 13  (NBS-039: 3, NBS-040: 5, NBS-041: 2, NBS-042: 3)

  USER STORY:
  As a Village Officer, I can register a marriage between a husband and wife
  by verifying both citizens. The system enforces marriage rules and issues
  a unique marriage certificate.

  ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA:
  Given I am in the "Register Marriage" screen
  When I enter Husband NID and Wife NID
  Then both citizen records are fetched and displayed for confirmation
  And the system enforces marriage rules:
      MALE: can have multiple active marriages simultaneously → ALLOWED
      FEMALE: if has active marriage (status=active AND husband vital_status=alive)
              → BLOCKED with message: "This citizen already has an active marriage"
      FEMALE: if last marriage dissolved/unregistered OR husband deceased → ALLOWED
  And on approval: a unique marriage_id is generated by the system
  And marriage status = ACTIVE
  And a marriage certificate PDF is generated with both citizen details
  And the certificate is pushed to RITA API
  And the marriage is linked to both citizens' records

  TASKS — BACKEND:
  [ ] Create POST /api/marriages with auth guard (village_officer only)
  [ ] Validate Husband NID → fetch citizen (must be ALIVE + gender=male)
  [ ] Validate Wife NID → fetch citizen (must be ALIVE + gender=female)
  [ ] Marriage rule check for wife:
      SELECT * FROM marriages WHERE wife_id = ? AND status = 'active'
      JOIN citizens ON citizens.citizen_id = marriages.husband_id
      WHERE citizens.vital_status = 'alive'
      → if record found → return 409 Conflict with message
  [ ] Generate marriage_cert_no: MARR-{year}-{sequence}
  [ ] Insert marriages record (status=active)
  [ ] Generate marriage certificate PDF (pdf-lib)
  [ ] Push to RITA mock API
  [ ] Write Jest tests: valid marriage / female already married / male multi-marriage

  TASKS — MOBILE (Village Officer App):
  [ ] Add "Register Marriage" menu item
  [ ] Husband NID input + verify → show husband name, DOB, status
  [ ] Wife NID input + verify → show wife name, DOB, check active marriage
  [ ] Show "Blocked" screen if wife has active marriage (with explanation)
  [ ] Confirmation screen showing both citizens' details
  [ ] Submit → show generated marriage_id + certificate download option


